    "name": "Pj Sin Suela",
    "profile": "Pedro-Juan Vazquez Bragan (born August 5, 1989), known professionally as PJ Sin Suela, is a Puerto Rican rapper and doctor. Born in Ponce, Puerto Rico, he graduated from medical school in 2015 before pursuing a musical career. He is recognized for his socially conscious lyrics and his collaboration with Bad Bunny and Ñejo on the single \"Qué Es Tu Plan? \" which reached number 13 on the Billboard Hot Latin Songs chart in August 2018. The song also reached number 17 on the Billboard Latin Digital Sales chart.",
